10101.flavor: Loyal vassal of the old baron of Tridam. Currently a wanted man.
10101.name: Falibor

10102.flavor: Loyal vassal of the old baron of Tridam. Currently a wanted man.
10102.info: Add 2 strength to each non-Gold unit that appears on the battlefield.
10102.name: Falibor

112101.flavor: I go wherever I please, whenever I please.
112101.info: Return to your hand if you lose the round.
112101.name: Ciri

112102.flavor: A twist of a witcher's fingers can light a lamp… or incinerate a foe.
112102.info: Destroy the strongest non-Gold unit(s) on the opposite row if that row totals 20 or more strength.
112102.name: Geralt: Igni

112103.flavor: If that's what it takes to save the world, it's better to let that world die.
112103.name: Geralt

112104.flavor: Men, the polite ones, at least, would call me a monster. A blood–drinking freak.
112104.info: When removed from the battlefield, transform into Regis: Higher Vampire and play.
112104.name: Regis

112105.flavor: He becomes invisible at will. His glance hypnotizes into a deep sleep. He then drinks his fill, turns into a bat and flies off. Altogether uncouth.
112105.name: Regis: Higher Vampire

112106.flavor: I can take care of myself. Trust me.
112106.info: Remove 4 strength from an opposing unit.
112106.name: Triss Merigold

112107.flavor: Also calls himself Borkh Three Jackdaws… he's not the best at names.
112107.info: After 3 turns, destroy the strongest non-Gold unit(s) twice in a row.
112107.name: Villentretenmerth

112108.flavor: Magic is Chaos, Art and Science. It is a curse, a blessing and a progression.
112108.info: Spawn either a Unicorn or a Chironex card.
112108.name: Yennefer

112109.flavor: Apologies. My exotic pet's a clever birdie, but a wee bit lewd. Paid ten thalers for the beaute.
112109.info: Spawn one of the two Field Marshal Duda units.
112109.name: Zoltan: Animal Tamer

112110.flavor: Know when fairy tales cease to be tales? When people start believing them.
112110.info: When destroyed, move to your deck and gain 3 base strength.
112110.name: Ciri: Dash

112111.flavor: A blast of concentrated energy that pummels everything in its path. Great for when you forget your keys.
112111.info: Move all non-Gold units on the opposite row one row back. Remove 1 strength from all moved units.
112111.name: Geralt: Aard

112113.flavor: A good sorceress must know when to conjure ice… and when to conjure fire.
112113.info: At the start of your turn, remove 1 strength from the strongest non-Gold unit(s) (except self) on the battlefield.
112113.name: Yennefer: The Conjurer

112201.flavor: A mimic, among the many other names for his sort: changelings, doublings, vexlings… or dopplers.
112201.info: Set strength to that of an opposing non-Gold unit.
112201.name: Dudu

112202.flavor: I'm a simple witcher, Wolf. Don't fight dragons, don't fraternize with kings and don't sleep with sorceresses…
112202.info: Play Vesemir and Lambert from your deck.
112202.name: Eskel

112203.flavor: If you're to be hanged, ask for water. Anything can happen before they fetch it.
112203.info: Play Eskel and Lambert from your deck.
112203.name: Vesemir

112204.flavor: Now that's the kind of negotiating I understand.
112204.info: Play Eskel and Vesemir from your deck.
112204.name: Lambert

112205.flavor: Never get between a mother dragon and her young.
112205.info: Choose a non-Gold unit three times. Remove 3 strength the first time, 2 the second and 1 the third.
112205.name: Myrgtabrakke

112206.flavor: The Master of Quartz Mountain, the Destroyer, Trajan's Slayer. In his free time, he likes long walks and candlelight dinners.
112206.info: After 4 turns, remove 1 strength from all opposing non-Gold units and return this unit to your hand.
112206.name: Ocvist

112207.flavor: At least you now know I don't easily lose my head.
112207.info: Resurrect at the start of the round and lose 2 base strength.
112207.name: Olgierd

112208.flavor: As time and space collapse before us, they expand behind us. In that way one moves forward through both.
112208.info: Choose a non-Gold unit in your hand (other than an Operator). Create an exact copy in both players' hands. Banish when destroyed.
112208.name: Operator

112209.info: When removed from the battlefield, spawn a Chort on the row where this unit was.
112209.name: Prize-Winning Cow

112210.flavor: Geralt, we gotta have a man–to–horse talk. No offense, but your riding skills? They leave a bit to be desired, buddy.
112210.info: Play on a random row from your deck or graveyard whenever a Gold card appears on your side.
112210.name: Roach

112211.flavor: Life without savoring the sound of surreptitious shananacking is like licking snails through a cloth.
112211.info: Move a card in your hand to the bottom of your deck. Create in your hand a base copy of another card of the same color randomly chosen from both players' cards (all locations). Banish when destroyed.
112211.name: Johnny

112212.info: Immune to Weather. Gain 3 strength each time a Weather effect appears.
112212.name: Sarah

112213.flavor: I might just discover I look great without ears… or hands. Apparently the King of Beggars accepts both as partial payment.
112213.info: Play the weakest non-Gold unit from your deck. Ties are resolved randomly.
112213.name: King of Beggars

112214.flavor: One of four bosses who control the city's underworld - the others being Sigi Reuven, Carlo The Cleaver Varese and the King of Beggars.
112214.name: Cyprian Wiley

112215.flavor: I remember so little… Yet when I think of my rose, I begin to recall what was.
112215.info: When destroyed, add 3 strength to all opposing non-Gold units.
112215.name: Iris

112401.flavor: They say unicorns are fond of virgins. Since finding a virgin these days is as hard as finding a unicorn, no one has been able to verify the theory.
112401.info: Add 2 strength to all other units on the battlefield.
112401.name: Unicorn

112402.flavor: Gods, that's no unicorn! That's…! – the last words of Vilemar, a famed collector of curiosities.
112402.info: Remove 2 strength from all other units on the battlefield.
112402.name: Chironex

112403.flavor: Knows one hundred words – eighty of them curses, the rest, connectors.
112403.info: Add 2 strength to all other non-Gold units on the row.
112403.name: Field Marshal Duda: Companion

112404.flavor: Zoltan's parrot had the extraordinary ability to irritate anyone who spent time with it. Including Zoltan.
112404.info: Remove 2 strength from all other non-Gold units on the row.
112404.name: Field Marshal Duda: Agitator

112405.flavor: A member of the Bovine Defense Force. Semper fi!
112405.name: Chort

113101.flavor: In the Final Age, Hemdall will come forth to face the evil issuing from the land of Morhogg – the legions of wraiths, demons and specters of Chaos.
113101.info: Spawn Frost, Fog and Rain effects.
113101.name: Ragh Nar Roog

113102.flavor: A djinn, good sirs, fulfills but three wishes. Thus freed, it flees to dimensions unknown.
113102.name: The Last Wish

113201.flavor: When you run out of peasants, decoys also make decent arrow fodder.
113201.info: Return a non-Gold, non-Relentless unit on your side to your hand, then banish.
113201.name: Decoy

113202.flavor: The sky dimmed of a sudden, and clouds amassed over the town. It grew fiendishly dark, and a cold gust swept in. Oh my, gasped Yennefer. We're about to make quite the mess, I think.
113202.name: Merigold's Hailstorm

113203.flavor: This ain't no normal storm. This here's the wrath of the gods.
113203.name: Skellige Storm

113204.flavor: The sorcerer Stammelford moved a mountain that obscured the view from his tower. Rumor has it he could only do so for he'd fettered a d'ao, an earth elemental.
113204.info: Remove 2 strength from all non-Gold units on both sides of the battlefield.
113204.name: Stammelford's Tremors

113205.flavor: An important part of every Witch Hunter's kit. In one muted flash, it turns the most powerful sorcerer into pork jelly ripe for cutting.
113205.info: Reset all units on the battlefield to their base strength.
113205.name: Dimeritium Bomb

113206.flavor: Behold Tedd Deireadh, the Final Age. The world destroyed by the White Frost.
113206.name: White Frost

113207.flavor: Plus one to morale, minus one to hearing.
113207.info: Double the strength of all non-Gold units on a row on your side, then banish.
113207.name: Commander's Horn

113208.flavor: The druid Vaedermakar controls the elements. He soothes storms into silence, musters destructive hail, summons lightning to turn foes into ash. So I advise you well… treat him with utmost respect.
113208.info: Spawn a Biting Frost, Impenetrable Fog or Torrential Rain card.
113208.name: Aeromancy

113209.flavor: A few of Alzur's monstrous creations roam the world still. Not least among them the horrid viy, who massacred its mage-creator and destroyed half of Maribor before fleeing into Riverdell's gloomy woodland.
113209.info: Play the strongest non-Gold unit from your deck. Ties are resolved randomly.
113209.name: Alzur's Double–Cross

113301.flavor: We stand not the slightest chance of incanting a spell so complex as Alzur's Thunder. It is claimed Alzur had a voice like a hunting horn and the diction of a master orator.
113301.info: Remove 7 strength from a non-Gold unit.
113301.name: Alzur's Thunder

113302.flavor: Behold Tedd Deireadh, the Final Age. The world destroyed by the White Frost.
113302.info: Spawn a Frost effect on both Melee rows that sets the strength of all non-Gold units on or appearing there to 1.
113302.name: White Frost

113303.flavor: The sun's shinin', Dromle! The sun's shinin'! Maybe there's hope after all…
113303.info: Spawn either a Clear Skies or a Rally effect.
113303.name: First Light

113305.flavor: A good commander's dream… and a bad one's horror.
113305.info: Spawn a Fog effect on both Ranged rows that sets the strength of all non-Gold units on or appearing there to 1.
113305.name: Impenetrable Fog

113306.flavor: Kills quicker than you can recite the Emperor of Nilfgaard's title in full.
113306.info: Remove 4 strength from all instances of a non-Gold unit on its side.
113306.name: Manticore Venom

113307.flavor: The beast rushed at them wildly, with fury in its eyes, immune to pain and any strikes the defenders could land. Nothing stood to stop it…
113307.info: Keep a non-Gold unit on the battlefield at the end of this round.
113307.name: Adrenaline Rush

113308.flavor: Epidemics respect no persons, no borders.
113308.info: Destroy the weakest non-Gold unit(s) on the battlefield.
113308.name: Epidemic

113309.flavor: Geralt took one step back. He'd seen men hit by Scorch before. Or more accurately, seen what remained of them afterwards.
113309.info: Destroy the strongest non-Gold unit(s) on the battlefield.
113309.name: Scorch

113310.flavor: Symbolizing spring and rejuvenation, the swallow lent its name to this potion that accelerates the rate at which wounds scab over and heal.
113310.info: Add 8 strength to a non-Gold unit. If it's a Witcher, add 12 strength instead.
113310.name: Swallow Potion

113311.flavor: The witcher's face changed… his mien turning inhuman, horrifying.
113311.info: Add 4 strength to all instances of a non-Gold unit on its side. If it's a Witcher, add 6 strength instead.
113311.name: Thunderbolt Potion

113312.flavor: Even the rain in this land smells vile.
113312.info: Spawn a Rain effect on both Siege rows that sets the strength of all non-Gold units on or appearing there to 1.
113312.name: Torrential Rain

113313.flavor: Some fight for Temeria. Other fight for Nilfgaard. I fight for the Heron.
113313.info: Double the strength of all weakened non-Gold units on your side of the battlefield.
113313.name: Warcry

113314.flavor: How much is a human life worth?
113314.name: Assassination

113315.flavor: Gaze long into the abyss, and the abyss will gaze back into you.
113315.info: Swap the strength of the strongest and weakest units on the battlefield. Ties are resolved randomly.
113315.name: Bekker's Twisted Mirror

113317.flavor: Many believe the empire's power rests upon the shoulders of its disciplined army and dutiful mages. In truth, the Nilfgaardian floren rules the world.
113317.name: Treason

113319.flavor: The mage's arms were twisted and bound behind his back. The Redanians gave the fetters a good shake. Terranova cried out, lurched, bent backwards, bowed forward, then retched and groaned. It was clear of what his manacles were made.
113319.info: Reset any unit on the battlefield to its base strength. If Gold, convert it to Silver (or Bronze, if that was its original color).
113319.name: Dimeritium Shackles

113320.flavor: Eat enough of them, and the world will never be the same…
113320.info: Spawn either a Mutagen or a Spores effect.
113320.name: Mardroeme

113321.info: Spawn either a {crd1} or a {crd2} effect.

113401.info: Remove all Weather effects and reset all weakened non-immune units on affected rows to their base strength.
113401.name: Clear Skies

113402.info: Play a random Bronze unit from your deck.
113402.name: Rally

113403.info: Add 4 base strength to a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield.
113403.name: Mutagen

113404.info: Remove 4 base strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
113404.name: Spores

114401.flavor: Best part about frost – bodies of the fallen don't rot so quickly.
114401.name: Frost

114402.flavor: A good commander's dream… a bad one's horror.
114402.name: Impenetrable Fog

114403.flavor: Even the rain in this land smells vile.
114403.name: Torrential Rain

114404.flavor: Plus one to morale, minus three to hearing.
114404.name: Commander's Horn

114405.flavor: Eat enough of them, and the world will never be the same…
114405.name: Mardroeme

121101.flavor: Don't need advisors and their schemes. I place my trust in my soldiers' blades.
121101.info: Choose a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield. Spawn an exact copy on the same row.
121101.name: Foltest

121102.flavor: A king should be merciless towards his enemies and generous to his friends.
121102.name: Radovid's Deck

121103.flavor: King Henselt did not look like a thief, but, with all due respect, that's really what he was.
121103.info: Convert all units on one of your rows to Gold until removed from the battlefield or the round ends.
121103.name: Henselt's Deck

121104.flavor: Don't need advisors and their schemes. I place my trust in my soldiers' blades.
121104.info: Choose a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield. Spawn an exact copy on the same row.
121104.name: Foltest

122101.flavor: I've not been a good father, I know, but… perhaps it's not too late.
122101.info: Spawn a Botchling or a Lubberkin.
122101.name: Bloody Baron

122102.flavor: A patriot… and a real pain in the rear.
122102.info: Remove 5 strength from an opposing unit.
122102.name: Vernon Roche

122103.flavor: That square should bear the names of my soldiers, of the dead. Not mine.
122103.info: Add 3 strength to 3 non-Gold units on your side of the battlefield.
122103.name: John Natalis

122104.flavor: Soon the power of kings will wither, and the Lodge shall seize its rightful place.
122104.info: Set the strength of all other non-Gold units on the row to 1.
122104.name: Philippa Eilhart

122105.flavor: Really believe you can dupe me with that tale you just pulled from your arse?
122105.info: Convert all other Gold units to Silver (or Bronze, if that was their original color). Gain 1 strength for each unit converted.
122105.name: Dijkstra

122106.flavor: I'm a medic. I tend to know what I'm doing when I prescribe something.
122106.info: Resurrect a non-Gold, non-Permadeath unit and convert it to Gold until removed from the battlefield or the round ends.
122106.name: Shani

122108.flavor: If I'm to die today, I wish to look smashing for the occasion.
122108.info: Give a shield to all non-Gold units on the row. The shield protects its bearer from one strength-removing effect.
122108.name: Keira Metz

122201.flavor: Dandelion, you're a cynic, a lecher, a liar – and my best friend.
122201.info: Add 2 strength to each non-Gold unit played on your side and 1 strength to each played on the opposing side. Does not affect spawned units.
122201.name: Dandelion

122202.flavor: Picture Dandelion in a dress and you've got the general idea.
122202.info: Draw 2 non-Gold cards. Play 1 and return the other to your deck.
122202.name: Priscilla

122203.flavor: Piss off! We aren't all philanderers. Some of us have depth…
122203.name: Thaler

122204.flavor: Better to live one day as a king than a whole life as a beggar.
122204.info: Play a Blue Stripes Commando from your deck whenever a Gold card appears on your side.
122204.name: Ves

122205.flavor: The Lodge lacks humility. Our lust for power may yet be our undoing.
122205.info: Remove 4 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
122205.name: Síle de Tansarville

122206.flavor: The Daughter of the Kaedweni Wilderness.
122206.info: When destroyed, remove 3 strength from all non-Gold units on its side.
122206.name: Sabrina Glevissig

122207.flavor: I once made a prisoner vomit his own entrails… Ah, good times…
122207.info: Remove 1 strength from all other non-Gold units.
122207.name: Dethmold

122208.flavor: He wears armor made of gold. Of course he's a jerk.
122208.info: Draw 1 card face up and 1 card face down. Keep 1, return the other to your deck.
122208.name: Prince Stennis

122209.flavor: Join me King Ravodid army. Order got – guard boatses.
122209.info: Remove 1 strength from all non-Gold units on the opposite row. Gain 1 strength for each.
122209.name: Trololo

122210.flavor: They said the queen was prone to outbursts, but I did not expect that…
122210.info: Destroy the weakest non-Gold unit(s) twice in a row.
122210.name: Pavetta

122211.flavor: I care only about what's good for Aretuza and my pupils.
122211.info: Spawn a Ban Ard Adept whenever a Gold card appears on your side.
122211.name: Margarita Laux–Antille

122212.flavor: Few know more about healing than Nenneke.
122212.name: Nenneke

122213.flavor: Drinkin' without Odrin is like rowin' without a paddle.
122213.info: Move to a random row on the same side at the start of your turn and add 1 strength to all other non-Gold units on the row.
122213.name: Odrin

122214.flavor: Forward, you sorry sods! Forward or you'll see the Nilfgaardians are the least of your worries!
122214.info: Convert a Gold unit to Silver (or Bronze, if that was its original color).
122214.name: Kaedweni Sergeant

122301.flavor: Never manages to hit the same place twice, which, upon further reflection, might constitute a real problem.
122301.info: Remove 2 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
122301.name: Reinforced Ballista

122302.flavor: Never manages to hit the same place twice, which, upon further reflection, might constitute a real problem.
122302.info: Remove 1 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit whenever a Gold card appears on your side.
122302.name: Reinforced Ballista

122303.flavor: Castle won't batter itself down, now will it? Get them trebuchets rollin'!
122303.info: Remove 2 strength from 2 opposing non-Gold units.
122303.name: Trebuchet

122304.flavor: The latest rage in assaults on walled cities.
122304.info: Gain 2 strength whenever a Gold card appears on your side.
122304.name: Reinforced Siege Tower

122305.flavor: I's a war veteran! Spare me a crown?
122305.info: Spawn an exact copy of this unit on the same row.
122305.name: Poor Infantry

122306.flavor: See this here tattoo? 'At's me, hackin' at a dragon. A DRAGON, m'lady.
122306.info: Add 1 strength to all your other Reaver Hunters, wherever they are. After 2 turns, play a Reaver Hunter from your deck.
122306.name: Reaver Hunter

122307.flavor: Haven't had much luck with monsters of late, so we enlisted.
122307.info: Choose a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield. Play an instance of it from your deck.
122307.name: Reaver Scout

122309.flavor: You gotta recalibrate the arm by five degrees.
122309.info: Add 3 strength to 2 non-Gold units on your side of the battlefield.
122309.name: Kaedweni Siege Support

122310.flavor: Blue Stripes and Scoia'tael are similar in one regard – hatred fuels both.
122310.info: Add 4 strength to a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield.
122310.name: Blue Stripes Scout

122311.flavor: I'd do anything for Temeria. Mostly though, I kill for her.
122311.info: Add 2 strength to all your other Blue Stripes Commandos, wherever they are.
122311.name: Blue Stripes Commando

122312.flavor: Stitch red to red, white to white, and everything will be all right.
122312.info: Resurrect a random non-Gold, non-Permadeath unit.
122312.name: Field Medic

122313.flavor: Stay calm, everyone. And be alert. The true owners of those cloaks and beaver–skin caps might be elsewhere.
122313.name: Dun Banner Light Cavalry

122314.flavor: Always wondered – how the blazes do those lads handle nature's call…?
122314.info: After 2 turns, convert to Gold until removed from the battlefield or the round ends.
122314.name: Dun Banner Heavy Cavalry

122315.flavor: Feel that? The earth trembles each time Big Bertha looses a stone.
122315.info: Every 3 turns, remove 2 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit.
122315.name: Reinforced Trebuchet

122316.flavor: Temeria! Temeria! Gods shed all grace on thee! And smite thy foes with horrid woes, for all eternity!
122316.name: Temerian Foot Soldier

122317.flavor: I'll die for Redania, I'll kill for Redania… I'll even eat worms for Redania!
122317.info: If 3 or more Redanian Elites are on your side of the battlefield, convert them to Gold until removed from the battlefield or the round ends.
122317.name: Redanian Elite

122401.flavor: Admit your mistakes and bury them proper – else they'll come back to haunt you.
122401.info: Keep on the battlefield at the end of this round.
122401.name: Botchling

122402.flavor: I name thee Dea and embrace thee as my daughter.
122402.name: Lubberkin

122403.flavor: To compare the achievements of Aretuza's female adepts to those of the boys from Ban Ard is to realize that the fairer sex is superior in oh so many ways.
122403.name: Ban Ard Adept

123201.flavor: Sound the retreat! Regroup! And wait for reinforcements!
123201.info: Play all instances from your deck of a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield.
123201.name: Reinforcement

123301.flavor: Not wealth or fame but intentions true –– that's what makes a hero of you!
123301.info: Convert all instances of a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield to Gold until removed from the battlefield or the round ends.
123301.name: Promote

124401.info: Add {add} strength to all non-Gold units on the row.

131101.flavor: Have some dignity. You know how this will end.
131101.name: Eredin's Deck

131102.flavor: Paintings should convey emotion, not words.
131102.info: Set the strength of all non-Gold units on one of your rows to 6.
131102.name: Ge'els' Deck

131103.flavor: That is not dead which can eternal lie, and with strange aeons even death may die.
131103.info: Spawn a White Frost, Impenetrable Fog, Torrential Rain or First Light card.
131103.name: Dagon's Deck

132101.flavor: Some men cannot admit defeat. Some keep fighting from beyond the grave.
132101.info: Destroy all non-Gold units with 3 strength or lower on both sides of the battlefield.
132101.name: Draug

132102.flavor: Ladd nahw! Kill them! Litter the earth with their entrails!
132102.info: Immune to Frost. Remove 3 strength from an opposing unit and 1 strength from all other units on its row.
132102.name: Imlerith

132103.flavor: We never hunt in these woods. Not even if it means the whole village'll starve.
132103.info: Immune to Fog. Spawn a Fog effect and 3 Rabid Wolves.
132103.name: Woodland Spirit

132104.flavor: A favorite son who chose a life of villainy.
132104.info: Immune to Frost. Spawn a Frost effect and 2 Wild Hunt Hounds.
132104.name: Caranthir

132105.info: Draw 2 cards. Your opponent draws 1 card.
132105.name: Avallac'h

132106.flavor: There are more things in heaven and earth than all the world's philosophers have dreamt.
132106.info: Resurrect a non-Gold unit (can be Permadeath) from your opponent's graveyard.
132106.name: Caretaker

132107.flavor: How to kill a kayran? Simple! Take your best sword… then sell it, and hire a witcher.
132107.info: Destroy 3 loyal non-Gold units and add their strength to this unit's base strength. When removed, set base strength to 8.
132107.name: Kayran

132108.flavor: Why fight? There are much better ways to work off excess energy…
132108.name: Succubus

132201.flavor: Like a cross between a crab, a spider… and a ploughin' mountain.
132201.info: Spawn an Arachas whenever a unit on your side absorbs strength.
132201.name: Arachas Behemoth

132202.flavor: Their long tongues're for slurping marrow – and whipping prey.
132202.info: After 1 turn, banish all non-Gold units in your graveyard and gain 1 strength for each.
132202.name: Grave Hag

132203.flavor: Seen a lot o' ugly critters in me life – morays, lampreys, blobfish… But never nothin' like this!
132203.info: Remove 4 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
132203.name: Water Hag

132204.flavor: ”What have I done?” the mage cried out, frightened of his own creation.
132204.info: Remove 5 strength from an opposing unit.
132204.name: Frightener

132205.flavor: A fiend looks a bit like a deer. An enormous, evil deer.
132205.name: Fiend

132206.flavor: I'd be your best – and last.
132206.info: Play all Crone units from your deck.
132206.name: Crone: Whispess

132207.flavor: We'll cut you up, boy. A fine broth you will make.
132207.info: Play all Crone units from your deck.
132207.name: Crone: Brewess

132208.flavor: I sense your pain. I see your fear.
132208.info: Play all Crone units from your deck.
132208.name: Crone: Weavess

132209.flavor: We know little about what manticores look like: though many have seen them, very few have lived to tell their tale.
132209.name: Manticore

132210.flavor: A certain mage thought them cute. It was his fate that gave rise to the saying Don't play with fire…
132210.info: Spawn a Lesser Fire Elemental on this unit's row at the start of your turn.
132210.name: Lesser Fire Elemental

132211.flavor: Take heed, gents, there's nekkers under this here bridge.
132211.info: Create in your deck 2 base copies of a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield.
132211.name: Nekker Warrior

132212.flavor: Fled one time in my life. From the Ice Giant. And I'm not a bit ashamed.
132212.info: Immune to Frost. Gain 7 strength while on a row affected by Frost.
132212.name: Ice Giant

132213.info: When removed from the battlefield, spawn 3 Lesser Earth Elementals on the row where this unit was.
132213.name: DELETE

132214.flavor: Each Wild Hunt warrior has gone through a rigorous selection process, but Eredin's personal cavalcade includes only the most brutal and most ferocious of the Aen Elle.
132214.info: Immune to Frost. Remove 2 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit whenever a Wild Hunt unit appears on your side.
132214.name: Nithral

132215.flavor: He always grants exactly what you wish for. That's the problem.
132215.name: Gaunter O'Dimm

132216.flavor: Big, bad, ugly. Squats in the sewers.
132216.info: If possible, discard a non-Gold unit, absorb its strength and draw a card.
132216.name: Giant Toad

132217.flavor: Common harpies feed on carrion. Celaeno harpies… they feed on dreams.
132217.name: Celaeno Harpy

132219.flavor: Imagine a cross between a mole and an armadillo, but ten feet tall and with an appetite for human flesh.
132219.name: Shaelmaar

132220.flavor: Drinking the blood of the Continent since the Conjunction.
132220.info: Every 3 turns, banish a random non-Gold unit in your graveyard and absorb its strength.
132220.name: Katakan

132301.flavor: Fog creeps on little cat feet. Foglets creep over the bodies of their victims.
132301.info: Immune to Fog. Play from your deck or graveyard whenever Fog is spawned. Gain 1 strength whenever a Fog effect is applied. Destroy when moved outside of Fog or Fog is removed.
132301.name: Foglet

132302.flavor: Many primal fears lurk in the hearts of men. The fear of the mist is well–founded…
132302.info: Immune to Fog. Gain 1 strength at the start of your turn if on a row affected by Fog.
132302.name: Ancient Foglet

132303.flavor: Imagine a cross between a winged snake and a nightmare. Wyverns are worse.
132303.info: Remove 4 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
132303.name: Wyvern

132304.flavor: Ugly – nature's way of saying – Stay away.
132304.info: Play all Arachasae from your deck.
132304.name: Arachas

132305.flavor: These little guys are almost cute, if you ignore the whole vicious killer aspect.
132305.info: While in your hand or deck, gain 1 strength whenever a unit on your side absorbs another's strength. When removed from the battlefield, play a Nekker from your deck.
132305.name: Nekker

132306.flavor: If ghouls are part of the Circle of Life… then it's one vicious circle.
132306.info: Banish a random non-Gold unit in either graveyard and absorb its strength.
132306.name: Ghoul

132307.flavor: It's a griffin, just more… griffiny.
132307.info: Remove Weather from its row and reset all weakened non-immune units there to their base strength.
132307.name: Archgriffin

132308.flavor: They sat still on their horses, seemingly relaxed. He saw their weapons – short spears with wide tips. Swords with oddly forged guards. Battle axes. Toothed gisarmes.
132308.name: Vran Warrior

132309.info: Immune to Frost. Remove 1 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit and gain 2 strength if that unit is destroyed.
132309.name: Wild Hunt Warrior

132310.flavor: First the buffalo horns atop their helms penetrate one's view, then the crest betwixt them, and finally the skull–like face exposed beneath their visors.
132310.info: Immune to Frost. Play all Wild Hunt Riders from your deck.
132310.name: Wild Hunt Rider

132311.flavor: Lesser does not mean worse! – Master Istredd of Aedd Gynvael.
132311.info: When removed from the battlefield, spawn 2 Lesser Golems on the row where this unit was.
132311.name: Lesser Golem

132312.flavor: Griffins like to toy with their prey. Eat 'em alive, piece by piece.
132312.info: Move a non-Gold card from your opponent's graveyard to your own.
132312.name: Griffin

132313.flavor: Who would think that overgrown bats would have a taste for gaudy jewelry?
132313.info: Destroy a non-Gold unit on your side and absorb its strength.
132313.name: Ekimmara

132314.flavor: Though the witchman lusts for gold, for the smiting of a drowner thou shalt give him but a silver penny, or three halfpence, at most.
132314.info: Immune to Rain. Move an opposing non-Gold unit to that side's Siege row.
132314.name: Drowner

132315.flavor: There are many species of harpy, and all are kleptomaniacs.
132315.name: Harpy

132401.flavor: Have some dignity. You know how this will end.
132401.name: Eredin's Deck

132402.flavor: Cry 'Havoc!', and let slip the dogs of war.
132402.name: Wild Hunt Hound

132403.flavor: Relax, I know how to tame wolves…– Dunbar the Hunter's last words.
132403.name: Rabid Wolf

132404.flavor: A certain mage thought them cute. It was his fate that gave rise to the saying Don't play with fire…
132404.name: Lesser Fire Elemental

132405.flavor: They're easily mistaken for rocks. Many a troll's been unpleasantly surprised by gastric grief on that very account.
132405.name: Lesser Earth Elemental

132406.flavor: Fear not the shadows, but the light.
132406.info: Remove 1 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit.
132406.name: Shadow

132407.flavor: Lesser does not mean worse! – Master Istredd of Aedd Gynvael.
132407.name: Lesser Golem

132409.flavor: The fool paid heed to superstition, stuffed his ears with wax and didn't hear the warnings. He ran his ship straight into the rocks.
132409.name: Siren

133301.flavor: The witcher raised a hand and quickly traced a path with it in the air. The crowd's rumble rose, the stones flew thicker. Yet the Sign curved their course, pushing them aside. They simply passed their target, protected by a shield unseen.
133301.info: Give all instances of a non-Gold unit on your side a shield. The shield protects its bearer from one strength-removing effect.
133301.name: Quen Sign

133302.flavor: Damn, the filth's o'errun us… We need a witcher or there's no livin' 'ere!
133302.info: Spawn a base copy of all Breedable units on your side of the battlefield.
133302.name: Monster Nest

134401.flavor: We've an adage here in Skellige… At a good feast, mead and blood flow in equal measure.
134401.info: Set the strength of all non-Gold units on the row to {pow}.
134401.name: Grand Feast

141101.flavor: To live in peace, we first must kill. This is human oppression's cruel finale.
141101.name: Francesca's Deck

141102.flavor: The dryad queen has eyes of molten silver, and a heart of cold–forged steel.
141102.info: Return a non-Relentless unit on your side to your hand and immediately play it again.
141102.name: Eithné's Deck

141103.flavor: That doddery dolt? Ye cannae even tell if he's alive or stuffed!
141103.info: Play a Silver card from your deck.
141103.name: Brouver Hoog's Deck

142101.flavor: I care not for kings and their titles. In the east lives one who truly deserves a crown.
142101.info: Remove 1 strength from all opposing non-Gold units. Add 1 strength to all non-Gold units on your side of the battlefield.
142101.name: Saskia

142102.flavor: It dawns on them once they notice my scar: a realization of imminent death.
142102.info: Spawn 1 Commando Neophyte on a random row whenever you play a Special Card.
142102.name: Isengrim

142103.flavor: King or beggar, what's the difference? One dh'oine less.
142103.info: Remove 6 strength from an opposing unit.
142103.name: Iorveth

142104.flavor: With each arrow I loose, I think of my da. He'd be proud. I think.
142104.info: Return the strongest non-Gold, non-Relentless unit (except self) on each side to the owners' hands. Ties are resolved randomly.
142104.name: Milva

142105.flavor: Drinkin' alone's like crappin' with company.
142105.info: Keep on the battlefield at the end of each round.
142105.name: Zoltan Chivay

142106.flavor: Brokilon bleeds… and not even I can heal it.
142106.info: Resurrect a non-Gold Special Card from your graveyard.
142106.name: Aglaïs

142107.flavor: Famed for constantly prophesying the world's doom. Not much fun at parties.
142107.name: Ithlinne

142108.flavor: Time to look death in the face.
142108.info: Ambush: When the next non-Gold Special Card is played, cancel its effects, then destroy the strongest non-Gold unit(s) on the battlefield.
142108.name: Schirrú

142201.flavor: I know how to execute orders, so take your advice somewhere else.
142201.info: Add 4 strength to a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield.
142201.name: Dennis Cranmer

142202.flavor: I am a Sage. My power lies in possessing knowledge. Not sharing it.
142202.info: Ambush: When the next non-Gold Special Card is played, cancel its effects.
142202.name: Ida Emean

142203.flavor: We are the drops of rain that together make a ferocious storm.
142203.info: Remove 2 strength from all other non-Gold units on the row. Draw a card.
142203.name: Yaevinn

142204.flavor: I'd gladly kill you from up close, stare in your eyes… But you reek, human.
142204.info: Ambush: When the opposing player passes, add 2 strength to all other non-Gold units on the row.
142204.name: Toruviel

142205.flavor: Most terrible things I've witnessed? The Catriona plague, the razing of Vengerberg and the charge of the Vrihedd Dragoons.
142205.info: Add 3 strength to a non-Gold unit in your hand.
142205.name: Vrihedd Dragoon

142206.flavor: The path to freedom is paved in blood, not ink.
142206.info: Ambush: When the round ends, return to the hand of the current owner if that player lost.
142206.name: Ciaran

142207.flavor: Our mead smells rotten to ye, do it? Easy to fix – I'll break yer nose!
142207.info: Add 1 strength to all your other Dwarf units, wherever they are.
142207.name: Barclay Els

142208.flavor: Lady Eithné's daughter had inherited her sublime beauty and her wild hatred for all that is human.
142208.info: If possible, destroy an unrevealed Ambush card and gain 4 strength.
142208.name: Morenn

142209.flavor: Mona…? No… no. I'm Braenn. A daughter of Brokilon.
142209.info: Remove an amount equal to this unit's strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
142209.name: Braenn

142210.flavor: I hate you, dh'oine. You are all the same.
142210.info: Remove 1 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit whenever a revealed Elf unit appears on your side.
142210.name: Malena

142211.flavor: Better to die standing than to live on bent knee.
142211.info: Play immediately from your deck whenever there are 5 or more revealed Elf units on your side.
142211.name: Aelirenn

142212.flavor: I was there, on the front lines! Right where the fightin' was the thickest!
142212.name: Sheldon Skaggs

142213.flavor: Ever hear o' the dragon Ocvist? From Quartz Mountain? Well, Yarpen Zigrin and his band o' dwarves did 'im in.
142213.info: Keep on the battlefield at the end of this round.
142213.name: Yarpen Zigrin

142214.flavor: Love justifies madness in any of its forms.
142214.info: Gain 3 strength whenever a Commando Neophyte appears on your side.
142214.name: Ele'yas

142301.flavor: Sure, I'll patch you up. Gonna cost you though.
142301.info: Add 3 strength to all other non-Gold units on the row.
142301.name: Hawker Healer

142303.flavor: ”Hatred burns brighter than any fire, and cuts deeper than any blade.
142303.info: Add 1 strength to the weakest non-Gold unit(s) on your side of the battlefield (except self), remove 1 strength from the weakest opposing non-Gold unit(s).
142303.name: Vrihedd Officer

142304.flavor: They track like hounds, run like deer and kill like heartless demons.
142304.info: Ambush: When a revealed non-Gold unit appears on the row, remove 5 strength from all non-Gold units on the row (except self).
142304.name: Dol Blathanna Trapper

142305.flavor: Worked a pickaxe all me life. Battleaxe won't be any trouble.
142305.info: Remove 3 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit. If it is not destroyed, gain 2 strength.
142305.name: Dwarven Skirmisher

142306.flavor: I'm telling ye, we're born fer battle – we slash straight at their knees!
142306.info: Keep on the battlefield at the end of each round.
142306.name: Mahakam Defender

142307.flavor: No matter what you may have heard, elves don't take human scalps. Too much lice.
142307.info: Remove 2 strength from all non-Gold units on the row whenever a Special Card is played.
142307.name: Vrihedd Sappers

142308.flavor: I spit on Scoia'tael ideals, but not on their coin.
142308.info: Play a random non-Gold Special Card from your deck.
142308.name: Elven Mercenary

142309.flavor: Temerians, Redanians, all the same. Better off dead.
142309.info: Spawn a Commando Neophyte on a random row.
142309.name: Vrihedd Vanguard

142310.flavor: Take another step, dh'oine. You'd look better with an arrow between your eyes.
142310.info: Remove 5 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
142310.name: Dol Blathanna Archer

142311.flavor: The key's mixin' pleasure an' business – like smackin' foes and gettin' coin for it.
142311.info: Gain 2 strength for each Dwarf unit on your side of the battlefield.
142311.name: Dwarven Mercenary

142312.flavor: Elf, dwarf, makes no difference – long as they've got coin.
142312.info: Gain 3 strength whenever you play a Special Card.
142312.name: Hawker Support

142313.flavor: You mean to say the she–elf danced amidst the fray? Have you lost your mind, corporal?!
142313.info: Gain 4 strength whenever an Ambush is played.
142313.name: Elven Wardancer

142314.flavor: You might manage to hide from them, but once spotted, don't bother trying to run.
142314.name: Dol Blathanna Marksman

142315.flavor: I fight for whoever's paying the best. Or whoever's easiest to rob.
142315.name: Hawker Smuggler

142316.flavor: By the time we'd heard them, it was already too late…
142316.info: Return a Bronze, non-Relentless unit on your side (other than a Blue Mountain Commando) to your hand and immediately play it again.
142316.name: Blue Mountain Commando

142317.flavor: Only one punishment for disturbin' the peace in Mahakam: a hammer to the heid.
142317.info: Immune to Frost. Add 3 strength to a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield. If it's a Dwarf, add 5 strength instead.
142317.name: Mahakam Guard

142401.flavor: Many nonhumans, fed up with the racism and xenophobia they encounter in the cities, decide to join the Scoia'tael.
142401.name: Commando Neophyte

143201.flavor: You exact from the earth a blood ransom, ripping out its riches by force. To us it bloomed, bore fruit and gave freely, for it loved us as we loved it.
143201.info: Spawn a base copy of the last non-Gold Special Card played, then banish.
143201.name: Nature's Gift

143301.flavor: Careful…! One more step and you'll be turned into molten glass.
143301.info: Ambush: When a revealed non-Gold unit appears on the opposite side, remove 5 strength from it.
143301.name: Fireball Trap

151101.flavor: No one can replace Bran. Though they're sure to try.
151101.info: Discard 2 cards and add 2 base strength to them. Choose any card in your deck and place it in your hand.
151101.name: King Bran's Deck

151102.flavor: Nilfgaardians call 'im Tirth ys Muire, the Wild Boar o' the Sea. Use 'im to scare their kiddies!
151102.name: Crach an Craite's Deck

151103.flavor: No one knows how he got his nickname – no one's dared to ask.
151103.info: Remove 3 strength from all weakened opposing units and 2 strength from all other opposing units.
151103.name: Harald the Cripple's Deck

152101.flavor: Instead of mournin' the fallen, let's drink to their memory!
152101.info: Spawn a Lord of Undvik on the opposite side.
152101.name: Hjalmar

152102.flavor: They call me Sparrowhawk. Know why? Because I eat rats like you for breakfast.
152102.info: When moved to graveyard, convert to Silver.
152102.name: Cerys

152103.flavor: Only the ignorant dismiss the importance of myths.
152103.info: If possible, discard 2 cards and draw 2 cards.
152103.name: Ermion

152104.flavor: When the time comes, the cockerel Kambi shall crow and awaken Hemdall.
152104.info: After 3 turns, spawn Hemdall on this unit's side. Destroy Kambi whenever Hemdall appears on the same side.
152104.name: Kambi

152105.flavor: Skellige must have a strong king. No matter what it takes.
152105.info: Draw 3 cards. Keep 1 and discard the rest.
152105.name: Birna Bran

152106.info: After 2 turns, gain 1 strength for each unit in your graveyard.
152106.name: Madman Lugos

152107.flavor: Her true name's Astrid Lyttneyd Ásgeirrfinnbjornsdottir, but that never fit on any forms.
152107.info: Spawn Fog and Rain effects on the opposing side only.
152107.name: Coral

152108.flavor: Blood for Svalblod! Skulls for his throne!
152108.name: Vabjorn

152201.flavor: I'm near ready to puke from boredom.
152201.info: Spawn a Spectral Whale on a random row on the opposite side.
152201.name: Blueboy Lugos

152202.flavor: He'll not reveal his name till he's defeated. He's a troll errant, see?
152202.info: Gain 2 strength at the start of your turn if it's the sole unit on its row.
152202.name: Champion of Champions

152203.flavor: When a warrant says dead or alive, most bounty hunters'll just kill you. Not me. Should I catch you, you'll hang, and I'll tickle your feet as you expire.
152203.name: Djenge Frett

152204.flavor: I've gathered all the jarls together. Now make your case.
152204.info: Draw 1 card and discard 1 random non-Gold card from your deck.
152204.name: Donar an Hindar

152205.flavor: Hear ye now the tale of the heroic deeds of Clan an Craite.
152205.info: Add 2 base strength to all non-Gold units in your graveyard.
152205.name: Draig Bon–Dhu

152206.flavor: An archdruid, a master of alchemy, and the grumpiest old fart in the Isles.
152206.info: Remove 2 strength from 3 non-Gold units on your side of the battlefield. Gain 3 strength for each.
152206.name: Gremist

152207.flavor: Now let's drink to Emperor of Nilfgaard – may he die of somethin' hideous!
152207.info: Immune to Fog. Remove 2 strength from 3 non-Gold units.
152207.name: Holger Blackhand

152208.flavor: Some call her the Iron Maiden.
152208.name: Jutta an Dimun

152209.flavor: The vilest man Skellige's ever known.
152209.info: When moved to the graveyard, lose 2 base strength and resurrect.
152209.name: Morkvarg

152210.flavor: Tame? Och, lad, Skelligers might train bears, but that don't at all mean they tame 'em…
152210.info: Remove 1 strength from each non-Gold unit played on the battlefield. Does not affect spawned units.
152210.name: Savage Bear

152211.flavor: Fall on your knees and beg Modron Freya for forgiveness.
152211.info: Resurrect a non-Gold unit (can be Permadeath). Gain 1 strength whenever a unit is played from the graveyard.
152211.name: Sigrdrifa

152212.flavor: Strike his name from the Saga of Elders! No one dare grant him shelter or sustenance!
152212.info: Remove 3 strength from this unit, then from the strongest opposing non-Gold unit(s). When removed from the battlefield, spawn Craven Revived on the same row.
152212.name: Skjall

152213.flavor: The emperor also thought him an accidental king. At first.
152213.info: If possible, discard 1 card and draw 1 card.
152213.name: Svanrige

152214.flavor: The gods have spoken: a sacrifice is required.
152214.info: Move a random card from your opponent's graveyard to your hand.
152214.name: Udalryk

152301.flavor: In their ballads skalds claim you cannot tell a berserker changed in the heat of battle from a true–born bear.
152301.info: Transform into a Raging Bear if weakened but not destroyed.
152301.name: Raging Berserker

152302.flavor: Don't underestimate them. Even their young are damned dangerous.
152302.info: When moved to the graveyard, transform into a Bear.
152302.name: Berserker marauder

152303.flavor: Our clan's bards will sing of my deeds long after you're dead and forgotten!
152303.name: Clan an Craite Warrior

152304.flavor: Better believe we can hunt. Thing is, not much game on Undvik…
152304.info: Remove 3 strength from a non-Gold unit.
152304.name: Clan Brokvar Hunter

152305.flavor: Can see the fear in their eyes. Fear o' me… fear o' Clan Dimun!
152305.info: Immune to Fog. Discard all Clan Dimun Pirates from your deck.
152305.name: Clan Dimun Pirate

152306.flavor: Haul together, hoist the colors high!
152306.info: Immune to Fog. Gain 2 strength whenever you discard a unit.
152306.name: Clan Dimun Pirate Captain

152307.flavor: The queen is guarded by the hardiest and fiercest shieldmaidens Skellige's ever known.
152307.info: Resurrect all Queensguards and add 1 base strength to your Cerys unit, wherever it is.
152307.name: Queensguard

152308.flavor: The deeds of Clan Heymaey will go down in history.
152308.info: Add 2 strength to all other non-Gold units on the row.
152308.name: Clan Heymaey Skald

152309.flavor: Escape them? In the waters of Skellige? Good luck.
152309.name: Light Longship

152310.flavor: Modron Freya, the Great Mother, is the goddess of love, beauty and bounty.
152310.name: Priestess of Freya

152311.flavor: Remember me words – a good shield can save yer life.
152311.info: Add 2 base strength to a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield.
152311.name: Clan Tordarroch Shieldsmith

152312.flavor: Swords are for wenches. Get yourself an axe.
152312.info: Gain 2 strength whenever another unit on your side is weakened.
152312.name: Clan Tuirseach Axeman

152313.flavor: Friends we show heart, foes we show our axe. Remember that.
152313.name: Clan Tuirseach Skirmishers

152314.flavor: They say Hemdall's heart swells whenever the longships sail out on a raid.
152314.info: Remove 2 strength from a random opposing non-Gold unit whenever a unit on your side is destroyed or you discard a unit.
152314.name: War Longship

152315.flavor: So ye can hit a movin' target at two hundred paces? Me, too. In a storm.
152315.info: Immune to Rain. Remove 1 strength from 3 non-Gold units.
152315.name: Clan Brokvar Archer

152316.flavor: We are An Craite! What others buy with gold, we buy with our lifeblood.
152316.name: Clan an Craite Raider

152318.flavor: They'll shatter on our shields like waves on a craggy shore.
152318.name: Clan Drummond Shieldmaiden

152401.flavor: This master turned the isle of Undvik, once home to the proud Clan Tordarroch, into a sorry shadow of its former glorious self…
152401.info: Immune to Frost. When removed from the battlefield, add 10 strength to any Hjalmars on the opposite side.
152401.name: Lord of Undvik

152402.flavor: When the time of the White Frost comes, Hemdall will sound the call for battle.
152402.info: Destroy all non-Gold units on both sides of the battlefield and remove all Weather effects.
152402.name: Hemdall

152403.flavor: Ehh, too big for a humpback. That's a finback. A finback? With a snout that short? Those herbs've gone to your head!
152403.info: Immune to Weather. Move to a random row on the same side at the start of your turn and remove 1 strength from all non-Gold units on that row.
152403.name: Spectral Whale

152404.flavor: True though it be that the Conclave has outlawed necromancy, what is out of sight…
152404.info: Add 2 strength to any non-Gold unit appearing on the row.
152404.name: Craven Revived

152405.flavor: Now finish your soup, or a berserker'll come and swallow ye whole.
152405.info: Immune to Frost. When first appearing, gain 1 base strength if it's Round 2 or 2 base strength if it's Round 3.
152405.name: Raging Bear

152406.flavor: Don't underestimate them. Even their young are damned dangerous.
152406.info: Gain 2 strength for each weakened unit on the battlefield.
152406.name: Young Bear

153201.flavor: Those cursed sorceresses are stealing our thunder! Whyever should folk choose a procedure taking several hours, when some perfumed tart can solve their problem with a wave of her hand?
153201.info: Add 2 to the base strength of a non-Gold unit in your graveyard (can be Permadeath), then resurrect it.
153201.name: Restore

153301.flavor: A sight more horrid you've never seen… The poor soul lay shredded as the beast lapped up its blood from the ground all around.
153301.info: Remove 3 strength from all non-Gold units on a row.
153301.name: Lacerate

161101.flavor: They do not call me the Patient. Take care they do not call you the Headless.
161101.name: Emhyr var Emreis

161102.flavor: The summer sun reflected in the quiet waters of the Alba – that's Nilfgaard to me.
161102.name: Morvran Voorhis

161103.flavor: A sword is but one of many tools at a ruler's disposal.
161103.name: John Calveit

162101.flavor: Witchers never die in their beds.
162101.name: Letho of Gulet

162102.flavor: I'll take an attentive reconnaissance unit over a fine brigade any day.
162102.name: Menno Coehoorn

162103.flavor: There's never been a problem a well–planned assassination couldn't solve.
162103.name: Vattier de Rideaux

162104.flavor: His eyes flashed under his winged helmet. Fire gleamed from his sword's blade.
162104.name: Cahir

162105.flavor: We are all pawns on his board. Playing a game whose rules we do not know.
162105.name: Vilgefortz

162106.flavor: Magic is the highest good. It transcends all borders and divisions.
162106.name: Fringilla

162107.flavor: My mark scars the face of our future empress. That is my proudest achievement.
162107.name: Stefan Skellen

162201.flavor: A ball of fire? Why, naturally. Whatsoever Your Imperial Majesty desires.
162201.name: Albrich

162202.flavor: Nilfgaardian mages do have a choice: servile submission, or the gallows.
162202.name: Assire var Anahid

162203.flavor: Cynthia's talents can be deadly. She needs a tight leash.
162203.name: Cynthia

162204.flavor: Your death will be as painful as that of the pathetic traitor Windhalm.
162204.name: Rainfarn

162205.flavor: Warfare is mere sound and fury – diplomacy is what truly shapes history.
162205.name: Shilard Fitz–Oesterlen

162206.flavor: And hands off the girl! Whatever we may be, we're not savages.
162206.name: Sweers

162207.flavor: For a fire mage, he's not very… flamboyant.
162207.name: Vanhemar

162208.flavor: Discipline is the Empire's deadliest weapon.
162208.name: Vreemde

162209.flavor: Letho's got a plan… what could go wrong?
162209.name: Auckes

162210.flavor: We do what we must. I am not ashamed of that.
162210.name: Serrit

162211.flavor: Men require constant alluring. Mystique and refinement do the job quite well.
162211.name: Cantarella

162212.flavor: Astrology, hydromancy, haruspicy, ceromancy. Ovomancy, spodomancy, metroscopy, brontoscopy…
162212.name: Xarthisius

162213.flavor: I spit on spells and those who cast them, on destiny, on prophecy, on the fate of the world. I spit on elder and younger blood alike.
162213.name: Leo Bonhart

162214.flavor: Albaaa! Forward!! Alba! Long live the Emperor!
162214.name: Tibor Eggebracht

162301.flavor: Learned a lot at Braibant Military Academy. How to scrub potatoes, for instance.
162301.name: Daerlan Foot Soldiers

162303.flavor: The North has nothing with which it could surprise us.
162303.name: Spotter

162304.flavor: The world has known as many plagues as it has wars. Yet both war and plague always take men by surprise.
162304.name: Vicovaro Medic

162305.flavor: I aim for the knees. Always.
162305.name: Black Infantry Arbalest

162306.flavor: Not the best for taking cities, but great for razing them to the ground.
162306.name: Fire Scorpion

162307.flavor: The Impera Brigade never surrenders. Ever.
162307.name: Impera Brigade

162308.flavor: Members of the emperor's fanatic body guard fight to the bitter end.
162308.name: Impera Enforcers

162309.flavor: The Emperor will teach the North discipline.
162309.name: Nauzicaa Standard Bearer

162310.flavor: They call us Death's Heads. Care to find out why?
162310.name: Nauzicaa Brigade

162311.flavor: Pledge your allegiance to our Emperor, Emhyr var Emreis… or die.
162311.name: Alba Pikeman

162313.flavor: Want irrefutable proof of civilization's advance? Look at war. Man gets better at killing with each one.
162313.name: Combat Engineer

162314.flavor: But… but there's no justice in it! One does not kill the messenger!
162314.name: Emissary

162315.flavor: A spy? No, that's saying far too much. I consider myself more of an observer.
162315.name: Ambassador

162316.flavor: Two ounces of calcium equum, one ounce of rubedo…
162316.name: Alchemist

162317.flavor: This model specializes in slinging corpses and ripe dung.
162317.name: Mangonel

30101.flavor: The only good dh'oine is a dead dh'oine.
30101.name: Commando Leader

40101.flavor: Like a cross between a crab, a spider… and a ploughin' mountain.
40101.info: Set the strength of all non-Gold units on one of your rows to 6.
40101.name: Arachas Behemoth

40102.flavor: No one has ever entered that forest and lived to tell the tale…
40102.name: Ruehin

40103.flavor: Damn, the filth's o'errun us… We need a witcher or there's no livin' 'ere!
40103.info: At the end of your turn spawn a copy of your last played unit.
40103.name: Monster Horde

40104.flavor: Like a cross between a crab, a spider… and a ploughin' mountain.
40104.name: Arachas Behemoth

40105.flavor: Ugly – nature's way of saying – Stay away.
40105.name: Arachas

40106.flavor: No one has ever entered that forest and lived to tell the tale…
40106.info: Remove 1 strength from each non-Gold unit that appears on the battlefield.
40106.name: Ruehin

60101.flavor: Soldiers loyal to the old baron of Tridam left the city with Falibor, thus becoming renegades wanted by the law.
60101.info: Add 4 strength a non-Gold unit on your side of the battlefield.
60101.name: Falibor's Soldier

60102.flavor: The soldiers from Tridam had received only basic archery training and most certainly were not among the world's best marksmen.
60102.info: Remove 4 strength from an opposing non-Gold unit.
60102.name: Falibor's Archer

60103.flavor: The old baron treated poachers mercilessly. Luckily for Milaen, the old baron was dead and his men, desperate outlaws.
60103.info: Remove 5 strength from an opposing unit.
60103.name: Milaen

60104.flavor: Whatever caused this madness must have been terrifying…
60104.info: Choose a non-Gold unit three times. Remove 3 strength the first time, 2 the second and 1 the third.
60104.name: Derran

60105.flavor: Every scout bears the lives of twenty–four men in his quiver.
60105.info: Choose a Bronze unit on your side of the battlefield. Play an instance of it from your deck.
60105.name: Falibor's Scout
